# BFF-Only API Calls

All API calls must be executed through the Backend for Frontend (BFF) layer. Direct calls to backend API URLs from components or frontend code are strictly forbidden.

## Architecture Requirements

- ✅ All API calls must go through the BFF layer
- ✅ Frontend components call BFF endpoints only
- ✅ BFF handles authentication, data transformation, and aggregation
- ✅ Direct backend API calls are not allowed from frontend

## Forbidden Practices

- ❌ Direct `fetch()` or `axios` calls to backend URLs in components
- ❌ API calls in React components, hooks, or utility functions
- ❌ Hardcoded backend API URLs in frontend code
- ❌ Direct database queries from frontend

## Required Practices

- ✅ All data fetching through BFF endpoints
- ✅ Use proper BFF routing and middleware
- ✅ Frontend receives pre-processed data from BFF
- ✅ Authentication and authorization handled at BFF level

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Direct backend call from component
const fetchCourses = async () => {
  const response = await fetch('https://api.backend.com/courses');
  return response.json();
};

// ❌ BAD - Direct backend call in custom hook
export const useCourses = () => {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['courses'],
    queryFn: () => fetch('https://api.backend.com/courses')
  });
};

// ✅ GOOD - Call through BFF
const fetchCourses = async () => {
  const response = await fetch('/api/courses'); // BFF endpoint
  return response.json();
};

// ✅ GOOD - BFF route handles backend communication
// In BFF: app/api/courses/route.ts
export async function GET() {
  const backendData = await fetchBackendAPI('/courses');
  return NextResponse.json(transformData(backendData));
}
```